What you need to know:

The 34-year-old Uruguayan has scored 15 goals in his first season in England, including eight in his last seven games, to help United to second place in the Premier LeagueUnited boss Ole Gunnar Solskjaer had repeatedly stressed his desire for Cavani to remain at Old Trafford despite reports the striker was keen to return to South AmericaCavani's form in recent months has played a major part in that success, after a slow start to his time in Manchester